### Steps to reproduce
1. Open alphabet keyboard
2. Gesture type something
3. The gesture path not drawing, then try again the path appeared.

### Expected behaviour
The first time I gesture type something, the path should be drawn.

### Actual behaviour
Not drawn at the first

**Android OS version:**
Android 6.0 emulator
 
I debugged the source code, every first time, it was blocked at GestureTypingDetector.java

``` java
public boolean isValidStartTouch(int x, int y) {
        if (mWordsCornersState == LoadingState.LOADING) return false;

        for (Keyboard.Key key : mKeys) {
            // If we aren't close to a normal key, then don't start a gesture
            // so that single-finger gestures (like swiping up from space) still work
            final float closestX = (x < key.x) ? key.x
                    : (x > (key.x + key.width)) ? (key.x + key.width) : x;
            final float closestY = (y < key.y) ? key.y
                    : (y > (key.y + key.height)) ? (key.y + key.height) : y;
            final float xDist = Math.abs(closestX - x);
            final float yDist = Math.abs(closestY - y);

            if (xDist <= key.width/3f &&
                    yDist <= key.height/3f &&
                    key.getLabel() != null &&
                    key.getLabel().length() == 1 &&
                    Character.isLetter(key.getLabel().charAt(0))) {
                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }


```
the mWordsCornersState is always LOADING state. so the first time when I typing, the GenerateCornersTask has just begun to execute leads to no data for gesture detection.

